programme.title: Open the Doors: Hellfest
programme.desc: Go to ground zero of the colossal effort to put together Europe's go-to festival for extreme music. Every year, Hellfest raises its black flag on the coast of France and brings screaming hordes of music fans to experience three days of insanity. Witness the colossal effort and the army of crew required to build Europe's go-to fest for metal.

programme.title: Footwork and Fugues
programme.desc: When a dance group and an opera director get together to make music and dance the result is magical. A spellbinding fusion of Bach and breakdancing is born when dance group Flying Steps collaborates with accomplished opera director Christoph Hagel. As they hone their artistic vision, they open up about their day-to-day struggles.

programme.title: Colours of the rhythm
programme.desc: Helped by colourful lighting, two stylistically different dancers interpret the same music in their own way. Two stylistically different dancers interpret the same music in their own personal way. With the addition of colourful lighting, their moves create visual art that expresses the rhythm of the music.

programme.title: Rob Meets Levi Sherwood
programme.desc: Rob Warner travels to Palmerston North, New Zealand, to meet with freestyle motocross rider Levi Sherwood. Rob Warner travels to Palmerston North, New Zealand, to meet with freestyle motocross rider Levi Sherwood. The two talk about how Sherwood got to where he is at a young age and where he's headed.

programme.title: Close to home
programme.desc: Elias and Johannes Hountondji feel the pressure as they race in their home country of Germany. It's time for Elias and Johannes Hountondji to race in their home country of Germany, where friends and family will be there to cheer them on. But having so many spectators raises the pressure.

programme.title: ABC... of MotoGP™
programme.desc: From understanding the rules to learning the jargon, find out what makes this motorsport so thrilling. MotoGP™ is the premier class of motorbike racing. Get the lowdown on what makes this sport so thrilling. From understanding the rules to learning the jargon, here’s a crash course to get you up to speed on the basics of this elite motor sport.

programme.title: Choose Your Own Adventure
programme.desc: Discover a party experience where every turn leads to a new and surreal part of an unforgettable night. More of an event than a party, Choose Your Own Adventure is all about letting go and living life as it unfolds. Go down the rabbit hole during a surreal night filled with food, music, and art, where the only certainty is an unforgettable experience.

programme.title: Global Warming
programme.desc: GZA, the show's host, travels the United States to explore how scientists are trying to solve global warming. Host GZA’s journey to discover how we might out-think global warming takes him from a Harvard RoboBee lab, to an underground park in New York, to the world’s largest hurricane simulator at the University of Miami.

programme.title: Transportation
programme.desc: GZA, founder of Wu-Tang Clan hip-hop band, investigates the future of transportation. To understand the future of transportation, host GZA looks at self-driving cars, pays a visit to the inventor of a personalised solar-powered rapid transit system, and rides a magnetic hover board.

programme.title: Aconcagua: A New Chance
programme.desc: Runner Fernanda Maciel aims to be the first woman to climb up and down a 6,961m mountain in a day. Follow ultra-marathoner Fernanda Maciel as she travels to Argentina and attempts to become the first woman to climb up and down one of the highest mountains on the planet, the Aconcagua, in one day.

programme.title: ABC of... Cliff diving
programme.desc: Get to know the art of falling as the top divers give an inside look at cliff diving. Get to know the art of falling as the top divers give an inside look at cliff diving. Jumping from almost three times the olympic height these divers find a way to look past fear and take a leap.

programme.title: Rainbow Dive
programme.desc: Rhiannan Iffland journeys to the Australian Outback and uncovers more than she expected. World champion cliff diver Rhiannan Iffland journeys to the Australian Outback to rediscover her sense of self and love for diving and in the process uncovers a whole lot more than she bargained for.

programme.title: Jeffreys Bay
programme.desc: Kanoa Igarashi goes behind the scenes at the WSL Men's Championship Tour at Jeffreys Bay, South Africa. Join Kanoa Igarashi as the Japanese surfer goes behind the scenes at the sixth stop of the WSL Men's Championship Tour at Jeffreys Bay, South Africa.

programme.title: Sébastien Loeb: Off Roads
programme.sub-title: The WRC's best take on the Dakar
programme.desc: Sébastien Loeb and co-driver Daniel Elena made WRC history. In 2016 they took on a new challenge: Dakar. Sébastien Loeb and his co-driver, Daniel Elena, made history racing in the WRC, winning a record nine world titles together. In 2016 they raced together once again and took on a new challenge: the famous Dakar off-road race.

programme.title: The Hansen Brothers goes Höljes
programme.desc: Ever wondered what made Kevin and Timmy Hansen into who they are today? Find out what drives these brothers. Ever wondered what made Kevin and Timmy Hansen into who they are today, and what spurs them on to excel within their sport? Find out what drives these driftbrothers to thrive.

programme.title: Road to 55
programme.sub-title: The Drive to Become a Formula One Racer
programme.desc: Experience the 2014 Formula One racing season with Carlos Sainz as he strives to become a top driver. Experience the 2014 Formula One racing season with Carlos Sainz as he strives to become a top driver. Meet the team behind his success and feel his highs and lows.

programme.title: A Door in the Sky
programme.desc: Get to know the Soul Flyers and see what went into making a ground-breaking BASE jump happen. Get to know the Soul Flyers, Fred Fugen and Vince Reffet, who make history by BASE jumping from a mountain then flying right through an aircraft's door. See what went into making this ground-breaking jump happen.

programme.title: The Soul Flyers
programme.sub-title: A Door in the Sky: Extra
programme.desc: In a world first, the Soul Flyers wingsuit pilots BASE jump off a mountain and land in a mid-air aeroplane. Above the Alps, the Soul Flyers, Fred Fugen and Vince Reffet, make history by BASE jumping from a mountain, catching a Pilatus plane in their wingsuits, then flying right through the aircraft's door – a world first!

programme.title: The Leather Jacket
programme.desc: A bit of cowhide that never fails to stand out, the leather jacket is a style icon the world over. Made for bomber pilots, adopted the world over, the leather jacket is a true style icon. Kyle Ng gets punk in Tokyo, Japan, races around Brooklyn, New York, United States, and meets the father of the over-the-top 'championship jacket'.

programme.title: Budapest
programme.desc: Magician Adam Trent discovers that Budapest, Hungary, has a light and dark side. Can his tricks work in both? The first stop of magician Adam Trent's European journey is the party city of Budapest, Hungary. Adam wants to see the things that the tourists don't, but walking on the dark side has its risks. Can Adam's magic get him out of a dangerous situation?
